from __future__ import annotations

#editd by mani
LOAN_GLOSSARY_KNOWLEDGE_BASE = [
    "Business concept: Customer. Canonical table: CUSTOMER. Definition: A borrower or counterparty who receives credit from the institution. Business purpose: Represents the primary party against whom credit exposure is established. Notes: One customer can have one or more facilities.",
    "Business concept: Facility. Canonical table: FACILITY. Definition: A sanctioned credit arrangement approved for a customer, such as a term loan, overdraft, or working capital line. Business purpose: Acts as the contractual credit agreement and parent container for one or more loans or drawdowns. Notes: Central entity in the loan model.",
    "Business concept: Loan. Canonical table: LOAN. Definition: An individual drawdown or funded exposure created under a facility. Business purpose: Tracks the specific credit amount disbursed, pricing, and lifecycle status. Notes: A facility can generate one or more loans.",
    "Business concept: Loan Account. Canonical table: LOAN_ACCOUNT. Definition: The operational servicing account associated with a loan. Business purpose: Used to manage balances, repayments, and account-level servicing activity. Notes: Typically one operational account per loan in this model.",
    "Business concept: Credit Assessment. Canonical table: CREDIT_ASSESSMENT. Definition: A credit evaluation performed during origination or periodic review. Business purpose: Captures the institution's review of the facility's creditworthiness. Notes: Can occur at origination and during annual or ad-hoc review cycles.",
    "Business concept: Risk Rating. Canonical table: RISK_RATING. Definition: The internal credit grade assigned as an outcome of a credit assessment. Business purpose: Used to classify borrower or facility risk and support downstream risk processes. Notes: One assessment produces one rating record in this model.",
    "Business concept: Collateral. Canonical table: COLLATERAL. Definition: An asset pledged as security against credit exposure. Business purpose: Mitigates credit risk by providing secondary repayment support. Notes: Examples include property, receivables, inventory, vehicles, and deposits.",
    "Business concept: Facility Collateral. Canonical table: FACILITY_COLLATERAL. Definition: The bridge entity linking a facility to one or more collateral records. Business purpose: Resolves the many-to-many style business association between secured facilities and collateral items. Notes: Also stores lien order in this model.",
    "Business concept: Guarantor. Canonical table: GUARANTOR. Definition: A third party that legally supports repayment if the borrower fails to perform. Business purpose: Provides additional credit enhancement beyond the borrower and collateral. Notes: Can be an individual or a corporate guarantor.",
    "Business concept: Facility Guarantor. Canonical table: FACILITY_GUARANTOR. Definition: The bridge entity linking a facility to one or more guarantors. Business purpose: Resolves the association between facilities and guarantor parties. Notes: Supports multiple guarantors for one facility if required.",
    "Business concept: Loan Monitoring. Canonical table: LOAN_MONITORING. Definition: A periodic observation of loan performance after disbursement. Business purpose: Tracks behavioural and servicing indicators such as delinquency days. Notes: Multiple monitoring records can exist for one loan over time.",
    "Business concept: Default Event. Canonical table: DEFAULT_EVENT. Definition: A formal record that a loan has entered default status. Business purpose: Marks a significant credit deterioration or failure to meet repayment obligations. Notes: A loan may or may not have a default event in this model.",
    "Business concept: Recovery Event. Canonical table: RECOVERY_EVENT. Definition: A post-default action or cashflow collected against a defaulted loan. Business purpose: Captures the recovery process after default, including settlement, legal recovery, or collateral sale. Notes: Multiple recovery events can occur for one default event.",
    "Business concept: Provision. Canonical table: PROVISION. Definition: A period-end expected or recognized credit loss amount for a facility. Business purpose: Supports accounting and risk reporting by recording loss allowance over time. Notes: Includes stage-based provision amounts in this model.",
    "Business concept: Delinquency Days (DPD). Canonical table: LOAN_MONITORING. Definition: The number of days a payment obligation is overdue. Business purpose: Used to monitor arrears and identify early warning signs or default risk. Notes: Also referred to as Days Past Due.",
    "Business concept: Stage. Canonical table: PROVISION. Definition: A credit impairment classification used for provisioning. Business purpose: Distinguishes performing, underperforming, and credit-impaired exposures for loss estimation. Notes: This synthetic model includes Stage 1, Stage 2, and Stage 3 values.",
    "Business concept: Sanctioned Amount. Canonical table: FACILITY. Definition: The approved credit limit or facility size granted to the customer. Business purpose: Defines the maximum contractual exposure approved under the facility. Notes: A loan amount may be lower than the sanctioned amount.",
    "Business concept: Outstanding Balance. Canonical table: LOAN_ACCOUNT. Definition: The unpaid balance currently owed on the loan account. Business purpose: Represents the remaining amount subject to repayment and monitoring. Notes: This can reduce over time as repayments occur.",
    "Table summary: CUSTOMER represents Customer. Primary key: customer_id. Business attributes: customer_name means display name of the borrower or counterparty; customer_type means segment of the customer such as Retail, SME, or Corporate; date_of_birth means date of birth of the customer. Examples: customer_id example C00001; customer_name example Aarav Sharma; customer_type example Retail.",
    "Table summary: FACILITY represents Facility. Related business terms: Sanctioned Amount. Primary key: facility_id. Foreign keys: customer_id references CUSTOMER.customer_id. Business attributes: facility_type means type of sanctioned credit arrangement; sanctioned_amount means approved amount or limit for the facility; start_date means facility effective or start date; maturity_date means scheduled end or maturity date of the facility. Examples: facility_id example F00001; customer_id example C00001; facility_type example Term Loan.",
    "Table summary: LOAN represents Loan. Primary key: loan_id. Foreign keys: facility_id references FACILITY.facility_id. Business attributes: loan_amount means amount disbursed for the individual loan; interest_rate means contractual pricing rate associated with the loan; disbursement_date means date on which the loan amount was funded or made available; loan_status means lifecycle status of the loan. Examples: loan_id example L00001; facility_id example F00001; loan_amount example 650000.",
    "Table summary: LOAN_ACCOUNT represents Loan Account. Related business terms: Outstanding Balance. Primary key: loan_account_id. Foreign keys: loan_id references LOAN.loan_id. Business attributes: account_number means operational account number used for servicing; outstanding_balance means current unpaid balance on the loan account; last_payment_date means most recent payment date recorded on the loan account. Examples: loan_account_id example LA00001; loan_id example L00001; account_number example ACC300001.",
    "Table summary: CREDIT_ASSESSMENT represents Credit Assessment. Primary key: assessment_id. Foreign keys: facility_id references FACILITY.facility_id. Business attributes: assessment_date means date on which the assessment was performed; assessment_type means type of assessment such as Initial, Annual Review, or Ad-hoc Review; assessed_by means credit analyst or risk officer responsible for the assessment. Examples: assessment_id example A00001; facility_id example F00001; assessment_date example 2024-01-05.",
    "Table summary: RISK_RATING represents Risk Rating. Primary key: risk_rating_id. Foreign keys: assessment_id references CREDIT_ASSESSMENT.assessment_id. Business attributes: rating_code means internal grade assigned to the assessed facility; rating_description means text description of the assigned internal grade; rating_date means date on which the rating became effective. Examples: risk_rating_id example R00001; assessment_id example A00001; rating_code example BBB.",
    "Table summary: COLLATERAL represents Collateral. Primary key: collateral_id. Business attributes: collateral_type means type of pledged security; collateral_value means assessed value of the collateral at valuation date; valuation_date means date on which the collateral was valued. Examples: collateral_id example CL00001; collateral_type example Property; collateral_value example 1500000.",
    "Table summary: FACILITY_COLLATERAL represents Facility Collateral. Primary key: facility_collateral_id. Foreign keys: facility_id references FACILITY.facility_id; collateral_id references COLLATERAL.collateral_id. Business attributes: lien_order means priority of the institution's charge over the collateral. Examples: facility_collateral_id example FC00001; facility_id example F00001; collateral_id example CL00001.",
    "Table summary: GUARANTOR represents Guarantor. Primary key: guarantor_id. Business attributes: guarantor_name means name of the guarantor party; guarantor_type means type of guarantor such as Individual or Corporate. Examples: guarantor_id example G00001; guarantor_name example Priya Mehta; guarantor_type example Individual.",
    "Table summary: FACILITY_GUARANTOR represents Facility Guarantor. Primary key: facility_guarantor_id. Foreign keys: facility_id references FACILITY.facility_id; guarantor_id references GUARANTOR.guarantor_id. Examples: facility_guarantor_id example FG00001; facility_id example F00001; guarantor_id example G00001.",
    "Table summary: LOAN_MONITORING represents Loan Monitoring. Related business terms: Delinquency Days, DPD. Primary key: monitoring_id. Foreign keys: loan_id references LOAN.loan_id. Business attributes: monitoring_date means date of the monitoring observation or snapshot; delinquency_days means number of days the loan payment is overdue at monitoring date; remarks means short note summarizing the monitoring observation. Examples: monitoring_id example M000001; loan_id example L00001; monitoring_date example 2024-05-31.",
    "Table summary: DEFAULT_EVENT represents Default Event. Primary key: default_id. Foreign keys: loan_id references LOAN.loan_id. Business attributes: default_date means date on which the loan entered default; default_reason means business reason associated with the default event. Examples: default_id example D00001; loan_id example L00001; default_date example 2025-06-30.",
    "Table summary: RECOVERY_EVENT represents Recovery Event. Primary key: recovery_id. Foreign keys: default_id references DEFAULT_EVENT.default_id. Business attributes: recovery_date means date on which the recovery action or cashflow occurred; recovery_amount means amount recovered through cash, legal action, sale, or settlement; recovery_type means type of recovery action recorded. Examples: recovery_id example RC000001; default_id example D00001; recovery_date example 2025-10-15.",
    "Table summary: PROVISION represents Provision. Related business terms: Stage. Primary key: provision_id. Foreign keys: facility_id references FACILITY.facility_id. Business attributes: provision_date means reporting date for the provision amount; stage means impairment stage associated with the provision record; provision_amount means recognized or expected credit loss amount for the facility at provision date. Examples: provision_id example P000001; facility_id example F00001; provision_date example 2025-12-31.",
    "Relationship rule: CUSTOMER to FACILITY. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: One customer can own multiple facilities and each facility belongs to one customer.",
    "Relationship rule: FACILITY to LOAN. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: One facility can generate multiple loans or drawdowns and each loan belongs to one facility.",
    "Relationship rule: LOAN to LOAN_ACCOUNT. Cardinality: 1:1. Business rule: Each loan has one servicing loan account in this model.",
    "Relationship rule: FACILITY to CREDIT_ASSESSMENT. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: Multiple assessments can be recorded for one facility over time.",
    "Relationship rule: CREDIT_ASSESSMENT to RISK_RATING. Cardinality: 1:1. Business rule: Each assessment produces one rating in this model.",
    "Relationship rule: FACILITY to FACILITY_COLLATERAL. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A facility can be linked to zero, one, or many collateral records through the bridge table.",
    "Relationship rule: COLLATERAL to FACILITY_COLLATERAL. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A collateral record can support the facility-collateral relationship.",
    "Relationship rule: FACILITY to FACILITY_GUARANTOR. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A facility can be linked to zero, one, or many guarantors through the bridge table.",
    "Relationship rule: GUARANTOR to FACILITY_GUARANTOR. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A guarantor can appear in one or more facility-guarantor relationships.",
    "Relationship rule: LOAN to LOAN_MONITORING. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A loan can have multiple monitoring snapshots or observations.",
    "Relationship rule: LOAN to DEFAULT_EVENT. Cardinality: 0:1. Business rule: A loan may not default, and if it defaults one default event is recorded in this model.",
    "Relationship rule: DEFAULT_EVENT to RECOVERY_EVENT. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A default event can lead to multiple recoveries over time.",
    "Relationship rule: FACILITY to PROVISION. Cardinality: 1:M. Business rule: A facility can have multiple provision snapshots across reporting dates.",
]
